</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E3F5283A-1A0E-4DA1-BDA9-D321A2DB8D56" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9BC64A02-078F-40CE-9DD0-55733BAAE2C8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9BC64A02-078F-40CE-9DD0-55733BAAE2C8-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3A1FB88D-EDD1-4A66-88A3-B86B3DF228E0" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-350AAFED-ACE8-405D-85AE-C4994962C629-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-350AAFED-ACE8-405D-85AE-C4994962C629-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Sharp yellow lines visible in the carriage direction 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">One or multiple lines per media step/swath 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Only visible in 1 primary color and its mixed colors 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Visibility of the yellow lines decrease with slower print modes 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> From a distance the appearance can look be very similar to 
<xref keyref="PQ_25" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7D1AA9F8-C042-4F34-A6C0-89D7688B29C4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors?>White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p ">The route to solve the presence of these lines is similar to 
<xref keyref="PQ_25" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7D1AA9F8-C042-4F34-A6C0-89D7688B29C4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors?>White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Please use the flowchart described in that document. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-D81DC64F-E5CE-437D-912A-6717FCDB058A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p "> See 
<xref keyref="PQ_25" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7D1AA9F8-C042-4F34-A6C0-89D7688B29C4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors?>White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors</xref> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">A thin yellow line might be misinterpreted as a malfunctioning yellow-printhead. However this thin line is printed by design. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case a nozzle fails during printing the NozzleFailureCompensation algorithm (NFC) is able to compensate this failing nozzle by using a redundant nozzle from another printhead or array. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However is some cases this NFC-algorithm is not able to compensate all failing nozzles. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In those cases the media below the ink-layer (mostly white) can be seen as no nozzle is jetting ink on that spot. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This will result is very thin sharp line. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As the contrast between the printed image and the color of the media is mostly very big this sharp line is easy to determine. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As a solution to minimize the visibility of a non-compensated nozzle yellow ink will be printed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This means the media is not visible but a thin yellow line. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
